Bring a large #pot{} of water to the boil with a pinch of @salt{}. Add the @freekeh{1%cup} and continue to boil gently for ~{12%minutes}. Drain, cover with a #tea towel{} and keep to one side until everything else is ready.

Remove the core from the @red pepper{1} and chop into small cubes ½cm thick, if your knife skills allow. Finely slice the @spring onion{4}. Pick the @mint{3%sprigs} and @coriander{3%sprigs} leaves and then roughly chop the leaves.

Make a dressing using the zest and juice of the @lemon{½}(zested and juiced), a pinch of @salt{}, the @za'atar{1%tsp} spice and the @olive oil{2%tbsp}. Give it all a good whisk.

Mix your freekeh with the chopped red pepper, spring onion, mint, coriander, @pomegranate seeds{1} and half your dressing. Taste for seasoning and add more @salt{} and @pepper{} to your liking.

Divide the salad between your #bowls{} and top with crumbled @feta cheese{1} and a drizzle more of your dressing.

> Freekeh is a grain that's very popular in Italy - you'll usually find it in soups and salads. It's got a good kick of fibre, iron and even some zinc but most importantly, it has the perfect taste and texture for this healthy July dinner.